'''''Big Open Skull''''' is an outdoor 1966–1973 [[bronze sculpture]] by [[Jack Zajac]], installed outside the [[San Diego Museum of Art]] in [[San Diego]]'s [[Balboa Park (San Diego)|Balboa Park]], in the [[U.S. state]] of California.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/entertainment/visual-arts/sdut-san-diego-museum-of-art-open-air-2016mar12-htmlstory.html |title=At SDMA, a move from the vault to the open air |newspaper=[[The San Diego Union-Tribune]] |date=2016-03-12 |accessdate=2016-09-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.balboaparkcommons.org/objectview/item/26042632/Art-of-The-Americas |title=Balboa Park Commons Objectview |website=Balboaparkcommons.org |date=1929-12-13 |accessdate=2016-09-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/sdma/status/707747935476391936 |title=SD Museum of Art on Twitter: "Jack Zajac's "Big Open Skull" (1966-1973) Bronze. #ArtoftheOpenAir #SDMA #BalboaPark " |publisher=[[Twitter]] |date=2016-03-09 |accessdate=2016-09-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sdjewishjournal.com/sdjj/natalie-jacobs/art-set-free-in-balboa-park/ |title=Art "Set Free" in Balboa Park |publisher=Sd Jewish Journal |date=2016-02-11 |accessdate=2016-09-16}}</ref> [[File:Big Open Skull by Jack Zajac, San Diego, 2016.jpg|thumb|Big Open Skull by Jack Zajac, San Diego, 2016]] ==See also== * [[1973 in art]] * [[List of public art in San Diego]]
