{{infobox artwork | title = Staging Point | image = Staging Point - Rozenfeld.jpg | other_language_1 = Polish | other_title_1 = Punkt etapowy | artist = ''Rozenfeld'' | year = 1941 (?) | material = ink, charcoal and pastel on paper | accession = ARG 581 Ring I/277_1<ref name="cbj">{{cite web|title=Cykl pięciu rysunków Rozenfelda przedstawiających miejsca i sceny z życia getta warszawskiego|url=http://cbj.jhi.pl/documents/633608/0/|website=Centralna Biblioteka Judaistyczna|publisher=Central Jewish Library|accessdate=12 May 2016}}</ref> | museum = [[Jewish Historical Institute]] | city = Warsaw | width_metric = 15.8 | height_metric = 20.0 }} '''''Staging Point''''' ({{lang-pl|Punkt etapowy}}) is one of five drawings depicting the life of children in the [[Warsaw ghetto]]<ref name="Smerin">{{Cite book|author=Barry Smerin|title=Dziennik Getta - rysunki: z Podziemnego Archiwum Getta Warszawskiego / Ghetto diary - drawings : from the Warsaw Ghetto Underground Archive|date=2012-01-01|access-date=2016-05-12|isbn=9788361850090|location=Warszawa|publisher=[Żydowski Instytut Historyczny im. Emanuela Ringelbluma]|url=http://www.jhi.pl/publikacje/63}}</ref> in the collection of the [[Jewish Historical Institute]], Warsaw.<ref name="cbj" /> The author of the drawings is an unknown draftsman, but they are signed "Rozenfeld". The drawing was made, most probably, between autumn and winter of 1941 and commissioned as part of the [[Emanuel Ringelblum|Ringelblum Archive]] - which has been inscribed in the UNESCO [[Memory of the World Register]] in 1999.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.europeana.eu/portal/record/2063613/POL_280_007.html|title=Staging Point {{!}} Rozenfeld (name remains unknown)|first=|website=www.europeana.eu|publisher=[[Europeana]]|access-date=2016-05-12}}</ref>
The drawing is set at 5/7 Stawki Street, which was used to hold Jewish children arrested by the "[[Blue Police|Blue police]]" outside the ghetto district.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cbj.jhi.pl/documents/633619/0/|title=Rękopis Rozenfelda|website=Centralna Biblioteka Judaistyczna|access-date=2016-05-12}}</ref> The "staging point" was the place where arrested children would wait for their parents, who were obliged to pay a fine. Orphans would instead be sent to an orphanage.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Urzykowski|first=Tomasz|last2=Żuchowski|first2=Piotr|date=2012-07-21|title=Poruszające rysunki z getta: na wszystkich widać dzieci|url=http://warszawa.wyborcza.pl/warszawa/1,34889,12167114,Poruszajace_rysunki_z_getta__na_wszystkich_widac_dzieci.html?disableRedirects=true|journal=Gazeta Wyborcza|doi=|pmid=|access-date=}}</ref>
The drawing depicts a group of seven children arrested by the [[Jewish Ghetto Police]] for the crime of smuggling food.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Inwentarz Archiwum Ringelbluma|last=Tadeusz Epsztein|last2=ŻIH (corporate author)|publisher=Żydowski Inst. Hisotryczny im. Emanuela Ringelbluma|year=2011|isbn=9788361850489|publication-place=Warsaw|pages=261}}</ref>
